<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11598&amp;p=133543#p133543"><![CDATA[
There was an glitch caused by 2 Player mode where the winning player would switch high scores with the losing player during 2 Player mini battles. I brought this to infidelity's attention and he has corrected it within his SRAM patch. Since my SRAM is based off of his, I've incorporated the fix. Credit goes to infidelity for the fix. I had to put the code in a different place since the Japanese VRAM frames for fade-in took the spot where infidelity fixed this. (His patch v7 is not public yet; I got a pre-release of it to test it and mine is the first to fix this publicly.)<br /><br />Patch it to SMB3 v1.1 ROM. The CRC16 of the original ROM is = CF5C<br /><br />SEE BELOW FOR DOWNLOAD<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5262">ShaneM</a> — Fri Sep 05, 2014 8:21 am</p><hr />
